RM  15687193
RT  Ectoine-induced proteins in Sinorhizobium meliloti include an Ectoine
RT  ABC-type transporter involved in osmoprotection and ectoine catabolism.
RA  Jebbar M, Sohn-BÃ¶sser L, Bremer E, Bernard T, Blanco C;
RL  J Bacteriol. 2005;187:1293-1304.
CC  Ectoine, and its derivative hydroxyectoine, are nitrogen-containing
CC  compatible solutes that protect enzymes from the stress of high
CC  osmolarity. Bacteria may synthesize it, import it, or both. This
CC  transporter was partially characterized in Sinorhizobium, where it is
CC  encoded along with genes for ectoine catabolism. All subunits are
CC  homologous to various amino acid transporter subunits.
